						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#158;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#137;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#177;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#185;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#169;&amp;#239;&amp;#188;&amp;#129; (Mandolin Orchestra!) is a Japanese card game. The game was produced in a limited edition of ten copies, sold at the Tokyo Game Market December 2016.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Mandolin Orchestra! is for 4 players only. Each player is trying to assemble a full mandolin orchestra, needing six instruments (first and second mandolin, mandola, mandocello, guitar, and double bass). The cards show the instrument, a value, and a colour, according to the type of song that musician prefers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is driven by a deck of event cards. Another set of song cards tells the players what instruments and values are required to perform the song.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players can draft cards when they match their colour, and by trading with other players, they can get their orchestra together. Once a player can match a song card, they declare and the music begins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
